<br>
Returning to Neriak after a long, hard day of killing, I stumbled upon a young cleric.  She was dressed in very little tattered leather and such.  A beaten up, old staff was gripped in her hands.  I immediately took a liking to her name.  I struck up a conversation with her and found she was most genuine and innocent.  She was an almost exact duplicate of how fun loving I used to be in my youth.  I decided to give her some pieces of armor that I had no more use for.  Her eyes opened wide, stared directly into mine.  As she held the scarred armor, I could see the appreciation on her face.  I decided to take off my helm and formerly introduce myself.  She instantly commented on my beauty.  No one had done that for a long, long time.  Eventually our conversation came to an end.  Before I left the cleric in the battle field I made her a promise.  I vowed to bring her the great Glowing Wooden Crook.  A rare weapon such as this would greatly help her advance her training.  She offered to help me slay the keeper of the staff, but I declined.  I had come to take a great liking to Lexxii, and I do not think I would stay sane if her life should be taken by the horrors of this world.  <br>
<br>
Some weeks had passed and once again I found myself in the home forest of Nektulos.  With my sword sheathed at my side, and a large crook on my back, I saught out Lexxii.  I found her sitting on a log conversing with her fellow dark elves.  I immediately noticed she had become much stronger than before.  She was draped in full banded armor and there was a certain gleam in her eye.  She quickly recognized me and embraced me in a hug.  Her hands struck the crook on my back.  A smile crossed my face.  She took a few step backs with her eyes wide and her mouth open as I handed her the Glowing Wooden Crook.  I told her about the battle with the beast, and pointed the punctured holes in my armor.  Just then, blue sparks shot out from Lexxii's fingertips and flashes of light surrounded me.  Immediately I felt healed.  Her powers had increased greatly.  I am fortunate to have such a wonderful friend.  Her generosity did not cease there however.  She asked if I would join the ranks of her guild.  I had noticed the tag on her armor, but thought nothing of it.  I accepted her invitation and became a proud member of their alliance.  Once again I left Lexxii to her training and I set off for more information about the death of my family and the disappearance of my mother.  Much time has gone by since that day.  I have become much stronger and the path has become clearer.  I now stand amongst others that know my pain.  We call ourselves, Midnight Council.  <br>
<br>
 <p><b>Krystall Ecllypse</b> <br>
